HEADWORD: Alimentation
<hw>Al`i*men*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>alimentation</ets>, LL. <ets>alimentatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of affording nutriment; the function of the
alimentary canal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>State or mode of being nourished.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alimentiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
